# Transcribed from tc_nonlinear_diff.main.cpp, PART 1 ONLY: the deterministic
# same-batch add+remove removal-cascade hazard (2 batches on one database).
#
# Part 2 of the driver constructs 12 FRESH Database instances (seeds 1..12)
# and feeds each 40 PRNG-generated batches; one sidecar file addresses one
# database, so those 480 batches cannot live here. They are validated by
# expanding the driver's PRNG offline (same LCG, same std::set iteration
# order) into per-seed batch files and running each through the oracle.

batch
+ add_edge 3 1
+ add_edge 1 1
+ add_edge 4 3
end

batch
+ add_edge 2 3
- add_edge 1 1
end
